    <summary>AlephNote is a lightweight note taking client for Simplenote or Standard Notes (or simple local storage)</summary>
    
    <description>
AlephNote is a lightweight note taking client. 
It supports multiple backends (StandardNote, SimpleNote, NextcloudNotes, local, filesystem) via plugins. 
It tries to be light on system resources but still give the user lots of customization features. 

## Features
 - Support for (user defined) themes and icon sets. 
 - Automatically version control all your notes into a local git repository to ensure a complete change-history and a backup of all your data
 - (Additionally) synchronize you rnotes into a local directory on sour filesystem, so you can view/edit them with external tools
 - Emulate a hierachical note structure (putting notes in folder and subfolder) on backends that don't support that (eg Simplenote)
 - Custom snippets
 - Fully customizable keyboard shortcuts
 - Uses Scintilla Editor together with all its features
</description>

